snippet.textDisplay:
I like hearing you talking about how these things are done but I really, really don't get these films. This and Iron Man and the way they're made now is just so unappealing and uninteresting. They're so painfully, caricaturishly pro-USA that it's like the old cold war propaganda funded films and seem more interested in little in jokes and nods to the viewer than actual plot.

I've nothing against superhero films but this 'generation' of them always feel like old B-movie level stuff but with a much bigger budget and a much, much higher profit margin.


Not attacking those people who love them in any way, but I just don't get them at all.
